        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Interest_on_this_VC"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N18_VC_20_SK"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/50.083333333_14.416666666"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>Special air quality in high mountains; tradition of spa resorts in Slovak mountains and related territorial identity of high mountains with healing recreational stays for people with respiratory problems. In the past, mining and metallurgical companies from all over Czechoslovakia built sanatoriums for their employees in high mountains in Slovakia. The healing method is basically an outdoor stay at the fresh air and walks or some physical exercise. Land use systems related to this use are natural areas and forests. Popular use of Slovak high mountains which has been increasing every year.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


